# Week 3: Tech Stack Recommender System Using TF-IDF and Cosine Similarity

## 📌 Project Overview
This project was developed as part of the Decode Labs Internship Week 3 task.

The goal of the project is to recommend the top 3 most relevant career paths based on the user's skills using Natural Language Processing techniques.

Instead of using predefined if-else conditions, the system uses TF-IDF vectorization and Cosine Similarity to find careers that best match the user's interests.

---

## 🎯 Objective

Build a recommendation system that:

- Accepts user skills as input.
- Converts textual skills into numerical vectors.
- Calculates similarity between user skills and career profiles.
- Ranks career paths based on similarity scores.
- Recommends the Top 3 most relevant careers.

---

